result.name: Liu Yuan Pavilion

reviews.text: High end shanghainese restaurant. Kids chair available. Food was nice but the restaurant got too loud when it's full.
Favourite Shang Hai restaurant in HK. Must try the small prawns with peas and the crab rice.
Cozy place with nice Shanghainese food

One star is also a waste. 
A potty, horrible restaurant. 
The old server screamed and got angry, saying it was not his fault. He said what he should not say to the customer. Because I’m a foreigner. But I can hear, understand some Cantonese. And other young servers were smiling, enjoying at the sight. 
If things don’t change, they will face misfortune. 
Maybe already.
A very busy restaurant serving yummy Shanghainese cuisine. Try the drunken chicken and the braised pork.
